This doesn't really have an emotional core, though it tries its damnedest. The interviews are functionally just exposition dumps, and the effect of the anomaly is pretty apparent by the time you get to the lady with 16 kids. The whole throughline of this piece is emotional attachment the person I'm supposed to feel bad for has all of 5 lines and no other appearance in the article. It's just longer than it needs to be, and culminates in trying to elicit an emotional response without putting in the characterization or atmosphere needed for it.







